InfosecPrep

Target IP: 192.168.170.89

Scanning



There are three TCP ports open on the target machine: SSH, HTTP, and MySQL. I will start my enumeration with the HTTP application. It looks like this application is using WordPress.

Enumeration

Port 80: HTTP

When we visit this port using a browser, the webpage above is displayed.


Running gobuster dir -u http://192.168.170.89/ -w /usr/share/wordlists/dirb/big.txt -x php,html,txt gave me the result above. There are some interesting directories.



The secret.txt contains a base64 string. The result of this string converts to an SSH key after decoding it using base64. Maybe this SSH key is of the user oscp, as there is only one user for this box? Running wpscan against this port did not show anything useful either. There is only one user called admin, and I was unable to crack the password of this user.

Exploitation


And it worked. I managed to login as oscp with the SSH key I obtained.

Privilege Escalation


Running find / -perm -u=s 2>/dev/null shows interesting files we can use to elevate the privileges with one being /usr/bin/bash.


Using ./bash -p, I gained a root shell.

Flags


The local.txt once I obtained a foothold as oscp.


The proof.txt once I gained a root shell by using ./bash -p.
